Method `runWithRetry` will throw exception when 2 times retry failed. For schedule, if exception caught when executing task, would not set next task execute. So if we want task always scheduled, need catch exception for task manually. In your case, do something like:

    private void runWithRetry()
	{
	    try{
	    	Failsafe.with(policy)
	        .onRetry(r -&gt; log.info(&quot;Database connection failed.&quot;, r))
	        .onFailure(r -&gt; log.warn(&quot;WARNING- Database is unhealthy.&quot;, r))
	        .run(this::run);
        }catch(Exception e){
        	//handle exception, make sure no exception rethrow
