Collection Initializers only allow you to _assign values_ to the object&#39;s properties or fields. You can&#39;t access a member of a property of the object inside the object initializer as you normally would in other places of the code. Plus, even if you had that option, the list isn&#39;t even initialized so you can&#39;t call the `.Add()` method.

